     <td valign=top width=470>                                                              


      <center>
      <table border=0 cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width=475>
	    <tr>
         <td style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 10pt;" background="/images/bg_heading_blue_01.jpg"><center><b>Nekkid Gnome Race</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		 <td>                            
	                                   

	    <table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0>
		  <tr><td><font color="00dd00">Submitted by:</td><td><font color="00dd00">Feydakin Rainsong</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Event Date:</td><td>07/29/2000</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Start Time:</td><td>10PM EST</td></tr>
      <tr><td>End Time:</td><td>???</td></tr>
        </table>
	  <br>
	  <br>


          Azure Sky hosted a Nekkid Gnome Race several months ago, and just as the bulls run in Pamplona, so too must the Gnomes run in Norrath!<br>
          <br>
          The rules are simple.  Create a level 1 gnome character of any class on Prexus and be at the gates of Ak'Anon in Steamfont around 10PM EST on July 29.<br>
          <br>
          This is important:  Make sure your Gnome's name starts with the letters "Nk" as this is how we will track you (and check for cheaters).  We will be guildinviting the "Nk" gnomes for the race so that everyone can chat, and guildremoving them after (or guildremove yourself).<br>
          <br>
          Gnomes will all start at the same time and will run to the Arena off of Lake Rathetear.  Along the way, you may take any route you wish, provided:<br>
          <br>
          1) You receive NO outside assistance from anyone (no SoW, teleports, levitate, invis, etc.) that would give you a speed or travel advantage in any way.  There will be spotters along the way, and people keeping tabs on the runners' progress with /who.  If you are caught or reasonably suspected of having cheated, you will be disqualified.<br>
          2) ALL runners MUST not turn on /roleplay or /anon at any time.  If you don't show up in a /who list, you'll get a tell from a judge.  If you can't prove immediately that you are not anon, you will be disqualified.<br>
          3) ALL runners MUST turn in their newbie letters to the PoD in W Freeport (that's right folks, all the Nekkid Gnomes will be PvP from West Freeport on, adding an extra twist of danger).  If you finish the race and are not PvP (i.e., if your name is not red), you will be disqualified from any prizes that will be awarded.<br>
          <br>
          The event will end at Arena with the awarding of prizes and a PvP free-for all in the Arena, for any that want to stick around for mad-cap fun.<br>
          <br>
          There will be binders on hand at certain stages (W Freeport and Arena, at the least) for those that want to be bound for added security.<br>
          <br>
          FYI: In the last race, the winner ran the entire trek from Ak'anon's gates to Halas (through Kithicor at NIGHT, no less) without binding or dying.  We added the PvP twist to add some additional spice to things this time.<br>
          Prizes are not yet determined but will include several awards of plat, some nice items, and also a "booby prize" for the last finisher.  The last race saw some really nice prizes awarded, including several hundred plat, some 10-slot backpacks and a couple of nice weapons.<br>
          <br>
          For details, see Azure Sky's website: http://droz.net/eq/azuresky<br>
          </td>
		 </tr>
		</table>

		
		
